                <p>It was a difficult time of year, cold and unforgiving at the University of Northern Colorado. The Senior CIS capstone had begun and groups had been divided up. It was in this fateful instance that Connor Mong and Bradley Rangel first interacted. Little did they know then, but they were about to create an application that would forever change how we find events. After being assigned the immeasurable task of coming up with a concept to build as an end product, Bradley got to work. One of of the most challenging concepts on a college campus is to find out what is going on. From extensive experience in his social fraternity and time as a college student, Bradley knew this problem well. He knew the aches and pains of becoming lost in regret of missing these activities. Without a second thought he presented this golden idea to his group, hashtagmcb. And thus Involvemint was born!</p>
